                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/11526: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-08T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 8, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 8—9:41 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. A representative of a foreign Embassy stated this morning that a few days ago
                    42 Soviet planes arrived in Nanchang bringing about 100 Soviet flyers and other
                    aviation personnel, also that about 50 Soviet flyers are in Hankow and a number
                    of planes including an efficient pursuit plane. This information has not been
                    confirmed but is regarded as probably reliable.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Shanghai, Nanking, Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
